        "Open Source",
        "datasette"
      ],
      "_signal_feed_title": "Simon Willison's Weblog",
      "_signal_feed_url": "http://simonwillison.net/"
    },
    {
      "id": "e1d9e45b6e3710b1",
      "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Apr/1/datasette-enrichments-llm-2/#atom-everything",
      "title": "datasette-enrichments-llm 0.2a1",
      "summary": "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRelease:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-enrichments-llm/releases/tag/0.2a1\"\u003edatasette-enrichments-llm 0.2a1\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe \u003ccode\u003eactor\u003c/code\u003e who triggers an enrichment is now passed to the \u003ccode\u003ellm.mode(... actor=actor)\u003c/code\u003e method. \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-enrichments-llm/issues/3\"\u003e#3\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n    \n        \u003cp\u003eTags: \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/enrichments\"\u003eenrichments\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llm\"\u003ellm\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/datasette\"\u003edatasette\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
