    {
      "id": "31e6d99de8089376",
      "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Apr/1/datasette-extract/#atom-everything",
      "title": "datasette-extract 0.3a0",
      "summary": "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRelease:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-extract/releases/tag/0.3a0\"\u003edatasette-extract 0.3a0\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNow uses \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-llm\"\u003edatasette-llm\u003c/a\u003e to manage model configuration, which means you can control which models are available for extraction tasks using the \u003ccode\u003eextract\u003c/code\u003e purpose and \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-llm/blob/main/README.md#configuration\"\u003eLLM model configuration\u003c/a\u003e. \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-extract/issues/38\"\u003e#38\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n    \n        \u003cp\u003eTags: \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llm\"\u003ellm\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/datasette\"\u003edatasette\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
      "date_published": "2026-04-01T03:32:16Z",
