    {
      "id": "38c0100bab28d400",
      "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Apr/1/datasette-enrichments-llm/#atom-everything",
      "title": "datasette-enrichments-llm 0.2a0",
      "summary": "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRelease:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-enrichments-llm/releases/tag/0.2a0\"\u003edatasette-enrichments-llm 0.2a0\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThis plugin now uses \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-llm\"\u003edatasette-llm\u003c/a\u003e to configure and manage models. This means it's possible to \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-enrichments-llm/blob/0.2a0/README.md#configuration\"\u003especify which models\u003c/a\u003e should be made available for enrichments, using the new \u003ccode\u003eenrichments\u003c/code\u003e purpose.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n    \n        \u003cp\u003eTags: \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llm\"\u003ellm\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/datasette\"\u003edatasette\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
      "date_published": "2026-04-01T03:28:44Z",
