    {
      "id": "c461deda494f771e",
      "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Apr/1/datasette-llm-usage/#atom-everything",
      "title": "datasette-llm-usage 0.2a0",
      "summary": "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRelease:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-llm-usage/releases/tag/0.2a0\"\u003edatasette-llm-usage 0.2a0\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRemoved features relating to allowances and estimated pricing. These are now the domain of \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-llm-accountant\"\u003edatasette-llm-accountant\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNow depends on \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-llm\"\u003edatasette-llm\u003c/a\u003e for model configuration. \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-llm-usage/pull/3\"\u003e#3\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFull prompts and responses and tool calls can now be logged to the \u003ccode\u003ellm_usage_prompt_log\u003c/code\u003e table in the internal database if you set the new \u003ccode\u003edatasette-llm-usage.log_prompts\u003c/code\u003e plugin configuration setting.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRedesigned the \u003ccode\u003e/-/llm-usage-simple-prompt\u003c/code\u003e page, which now requires the \u003ccode\u003ellm-usage-simple-prompt\u003c/code\u003e permission.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n    \n        \u003cp\u003eTags: \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llm\"\u003ellm\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/datasette\"\u003edatasette\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
      "date_published": "2026-04-01T03:24:03Z",
